Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle to moderate turn of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp with prow symbol.
Type series: KT90 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names Ierokles, Aineas. Parallels are noted by N. Jefremow, Die Amphorenstempel des hellenistischen Knidos, Munich 1995, 197, nos. 533-543.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (296)
